soc: cix: keep USB-DP PHY companions alongside PNP0D10

The Sky1 USB ACPI arbitration prefers generic PNP0D10 xHCI controller nodes over overlapping CIX vendor controller nodes.  That suppression was too broad for CIXH2033 USB-DP PHY companion nodes, which own the Type-C mux/orientation-switch provider registration and do not describe the xHCI controller MMIO region.

Let CIXH2033 enumerate even when PNP0D10 exists so the RTS5453 ACPI graph can bind to real Type-C mux/orientation providers while still suppressing the overlapping vendor controller path.

---

diff --git a/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-usb-scan.c b/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-usb-scan.c
--- a/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-usb-scan.c
+++ b/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-usb-scan.c
@@ -53,6 +53,11 @@ static bool sky1_usb_vendor_present(void)
 	       sky1_usb_acpi_id_present("CIXH2034");
 }
 
+static bool sky1_usb_id_is_non_overlapping_companion(const char *hid)
+{
+	return !strcmp(hid, "CIXH2033");
+}
+
 static int sky1_usb_scan_attach(struct acpi_device *adev,
 				const struct acpi_device_id *id)
 {
@@ -68,6 +73,13 @@ static int sky1_usb_scan_attach(struct acpi_device *adev,
 		return 0;
 	}
 
+	if (sky1_usb_id_is_non_overlapping_companion(id->id)) {
+		dev_dbg(&adev->dev,
+			"Sky1 USB: keeping %s companion alongside PNP0D10\n",
+			id->id);
+		return 0;
+	}
+
 	if (sky1_usb_acpi_id_present("PNP0D10")) {
 		dev_dbg(&adev->dev,
 			"Sky1 USB: suppressing %s because PNP0D10 is present\n",
